ndational material for this process was classicism and its purpose was political. This delineates a new geography and chronology of a truly European cultural history. It also provides the key traits for the European cultural identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aCultural Studies. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistorical states and empires: Europe. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aItaly. 4aPolitical structure and processes. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aRenaissance, Court studies, Culture, Politics, Italy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048550944?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048550944423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048550944/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076709-4  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK